         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [With respect to the species which I had referred to,  ¶ Perotis ¶ , I have been informed by Dr. F. Mueller that it is the  ¶ Microlaena stipoides ¶  of Brown ¶  — a species which the doctor says r...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">58.03.00b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Woolls</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. For the text given here, see <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney morning herald</seg>, 22 March 1858, p. 8, in a letter to the Editor by Woolls.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[With respect to the species which I had referred to, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Perotis">Perotis</name>
               </seg>, I have been informed by Dr. F. Mueller that it is the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Microlaena%20stipoides">Microlaena stipoides</name>
               </seg> of Brown<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Robert Brown ((1773-1858).</p>
               </note> — a species which the doctor says ranges over New Zealand, South Australia, Australia Felix, Tasmania, and the whole of New South Wales. He also remarks, in allusion to <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Lepturus%20repens">Lepturus repens</name>
               </seg> (a grass which I have lately found growing even in General Macarthur’s garden) that he had searched for it in all his journeys without success.]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Woolls added: 'The deep interest which Dr. Mueller has manifested in the botany of the Parramatta district is a subject of congratulation to every one who is anxious to develope the vegetable resources of the colony, and I feel assured that any remarks which he may publish respecting our <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eucalypti</seg> or other genera will be read with great attention.'</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
